dc_description_s: Shows Westphalia, Hesse, Darmstadt and the Rhine provinces of Prussia. Relief indicated by hachures and spot heights. "Entered according to Act of Congress in the year 1855 by J.H. Colton ... " In margin: No. 114. Text on verso with caption title: Germany. No. VI.--Mecklenburg, Nassau, and Oldenburg. Probably issued in: Colton's general atlas ... New York : G.W. and C.B. Colton & Co., 1866. George W. and Charles B. Colton took over the business founded by their father Joseph H. around 1865. cf. Tooley's dictionary of mapmakers.
dc_publisher_s: New York : Published by G.W. and C.B. Colton & Co., no. 172 William St., c1855.
